Rating: 4
I have been making this recipe for years, but now I can no longer eat gluten. I have made this twice using gluten-free flours and it has turned out great both times. What a forgiving recipe! Also this time I cut the sugar from the 2 cups I used to use, to a total of 1.5 cups (3/4 cup brown and 3/4 cup white). I also added fresh chopped cranberries to the pumpkin puree for a total of 16 ounces. I doubled the cinnamon and nutmeg and added 1/2 teaspoon of ground ginger. Also used 1/2 cup of olive oil and 1/2 cup of apple sauce. In case anyone else would like to try to make it gluten-free I used a total of 420 grams of different GF flours (140 grams for every cup of regular flour). First I make a batch of GF flour based on the video from the Glutenfreegirl.com website. 1000 grams total: 300 grams potato starch, 300 grams sweet rice flour, 150 grams millet flour, 150 grams teff flour, 50 grams almond flour and 50 grams superfine brown rice flour. (Last time I used 200 grams millet flour and 200 grams sorghum flour along with the potato starch and sweet rice flour). Then I measured out 420 grams of the combined (and shaken) flour mixture, to replace the 3 cups all purpose flour the recipe calls for. You cannot tell this is Gluten Free! Plus you have some GF flour left over to experiment with. Good luck!

