Rating: 4
DELICIOUS pumpkin bread. Only made a few changes. 3 cups of sugar seemed excessive, so like other reviewers I used only 2 cups (1 white, 1 light brown). For vegetable oil I used coconut oil, which is extremely healthy compared to other oils. Also, I see a lot of reviewers cut the oil in 1/2 in favor of applesauce - which if you are trying to make this bread more healthy I would advise, as a nutritionist, to just use the full cup of oil. It sounds counterintuitive, but sugar (in this case applesauce) turns to fat in the body, not fat (the oil). Also I used gluten-free flour so I needed to add xanthan gum, which I used 1 1/2 teaspoons. Also, instead of walnuts, I topped my bread w/ raw pumpkin seeds that I candied.

Rating: 4
