Very nice. Good flavor, great texture. I would have appreciated a bit more pumpkin flavor, thusly 3 forks. Like others, I did modify the recipe to use one cup white and one cup brown sugar. It was plenty sweet--can't imagine what three cups would have tasted like. Also, the spices seemed out of balance to me--lots of cloves taste bitter. I used 1/2 tsp. cloves, 1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon, 1 generous tsp ground ginger, 1/2 tsp. allspice and a scant 1/2 tsp. nutmeg. I use freshly grated nutmeg, and a tsp. in any recipe will overwhelm it.I'll make this again, and next time add some dried cranberries. I might use chocolate chips, but they I'll omit the allspice and nutmeg. I don't like the combination of nutmeg and chocolate.

