Rating: 4
I love this recipe. It really lends itself to experimenation, freezes well and I have never made a bad batch. Basic Variation-- I always reduce the sugar to two cups (I use raw sugar so have never felt the need to use brown and white sugar). I did a blind taste test with my family and all including my son who loves sweets preferred the one with less sugar. I had a contest to guess what was different - none guessed that one had less sugar. Favorite Variation-- I up the spices 1 and a half teaspoons each and to add 1 to one and an half cups of pecans- pulverized in the food processor- then add 1 cup of chocolate chips (a mix of semi sweet and milk chocolate chips). The fat in the nuts makes it very moist and enhances the flavors of the pumpkin and spices. Kid/School Friendly Variation-- When I send this to school I delete the nuts. Because of nut allergies schools are very concerned about nut allergies (rightly so). To account for the missing fat I use either plain yogurt or sour cream to replace the fat and moisture from the pecans. Last year my son had a vegan in his class and I made a loaf using olive oil intead of pecans and dried cranberries instead of chocolate chips - it was a big hit - his mom wrote to me for the recipe.

