Rating: 4
I chose this recipe because I had a small butternut squash that needed using, which I substituted for pumpkin (steamed and pureed, it made a little less than 2 cups.) I had already mixed the 3 c. sugar and 1 c. vegetable oil when I realized I hadn't read the reviews. I stopped and read them, and the main thing that stood out was that the bread was too sweet when made as written. So I took out 1 c. of the sugar/oil mix, and instead of replacing 1/3 c. oil I added 1/2 c. unsweetened applesauce. Then I followed the rest of the recipe, adding an additional 1 tsp. of cinnamon and an additional 1/2 tsp. salt. I put nuts in half the batter and raisins in the other. Baked for about 55 minutes in two loaf pans. Delicious!

