Rating: 4
I make this over and over again, but i definitely modify it to suit my tastes. First, I roast my own pumpkin...slice in half, scoop out glop, rub in olive oil and roast at 400 for an hour, then puree. Next, I cut the sugar to 3/4 c white sugar and 3/4 cup brown sugar. It's still plenty sweet. I use one stick of butter, plus a half cup of either low fat sour cream or yogurt, depending on what i have on hand. And finally, I use 2 cups of bread flour and 1 cup of whole wheat flour, because I like it to have the texture of actual bread not cake. I've passed this on to tons of people and they've all loved it!

