Rating: 3
I made a more wholesome version by substituting 1.5 cups brown sugar and 1 cup molasses for sweetening, scaling back oil to 1/2 cup plus 3 TB butter, and subbing one cup of whole wheat flour. Baking soda went up to 1.5 teaspoons to make up for the acid in the molasses. This made a really good, rustic bread that's still sweet and moist (my husband couldn't stop eating it) and more appealing if you like hearty, rustic fare.

