Rating: 4
I love this recipe. I love it even more with these changes: 1) Try to find Asian pumpkins. Just cut the pumpkin into chunks (with the skin!) and deseed. Boil and puree in the blender. It gives the bread a better taste and texture. And you can use leftover puree to make pumpkin pancakes! 2) Instead of walnuts, use toasted, chopped pecans. 3) Sometimes I'll replace a 1/2 cup of the nuts with a 1/2 cup of dried cranberries. Yum! 4) My boyfriend likes if I put a 1/2 cup of chocolate chips in instead of the cup of nuts. I think that one is only for people who really love chocolate. Also, applesauce in place of the oil is just as good!

