Cannot praise this recipe highly enough. It's incredibly forgiving of experimentation and substitutions. I always triple the spices and add ground ginger. For some reason, I can only get 15 oz cans of pumpkin, and have added either yogurt, applesauce or sour cream to make up for the missing ounce. I've used butter, olive oil, and coconut oil in varying proportions for the shortening (coconut oil yielded the moistest, most velvety result!) I always use brown sugar as one of the 3 cups of sugar. Will never try another recipe again - this is the Holy Grail. Everyone raves about it. Makes an excellent hostess gift, too.

