I cut the recipe in half for one loaf. Wanted a healthier version, so I used 1/2 cup white and 1/2 cup brown sugar (omitting another 1/2 cup called for). Used 1 cup white flour, 1/4 cup wheat and 1/4 cup ground flaxseed. For oil, used half applesauce and half canola oil. Substituted raisins for nuts due to allergies. I was expecting a tasteless brick but instead got a delicious, moist, flavorful and even sweet bread. This was easy to make and yummy warm out of the oven. It was also done in 50 minutes.

