Rating: 4
AN EXCELLENT RECIPE!!!! I read over most of the comments written by others before attempting to make this recipe. I followed the suggestion of decreasing the sugar to 2 cups, as well as lowering the oil to 2/3 of a cup [I also added 1/3 buttermilk as one reviewer suggested]. I doubled all the spices too. I also added 1 tablespoon of finely grated fresh ginger. I didn't add the nuts though. I baked the cake in a bundt pan for the time indicated. The finished product is perhaps the moistest cake ("bread" if you want to call it that) that I have made recently. It is wonderful! I will definitely make this again. If I was making this again for company, I would change the sugar to 2 1/2 cups and keep the oil to one cup (as well as doubling on the spices). Options I would consider: chocolate chip pieces or maybe shredded carrots.

