My children love this bread (so do I)! I made so many changes though, I wonder what the original recipe would be like! I used all whole wheat flour, slightly less oil, only 2 cups sugar (raw, not white or brown), a 15-oz can of pumpkin, and I added ginger. Oh, and I left out the nuts (little kids, you know...). Somehow there was only enough batter for one regular size pan and a small loaf pan (maybe because I like fuller loaves). I baked the small one for 40 minutes and the larger one for 1 hour. Both came out beautifully. I will make this pumpkin bread again for sure and maybe increase the spices a little as other bakers have suggested. Great bread - hard to stop eating it!

