Rating: 3
Wow! This was good. Emboldened by the previous reviews, I decided to experiment to make this a little more health-conscious, since we're dieting but still wanted a good, welcome to Fall treat. Here we go: I used only 2 cups of organic sugar (which has a stronger, almost brown-sugary taste). Instead of the oil, I used 1 cup of Trader Joe's unsweetened, chunky applesauce. Non-chunky would probably work, but I really liked the big pieces of apple. I also used 2 cups of whole wheat flour & 1 cup of regular all purpose flour. I did a couple of other substitutions that have nothing to do with health, but what I had on hand: I used 1 bread loaf pan and 1 mini-bundt pan. The mini bundts were done in 30 minutes, while the loaf took about 50. Also, I took the advice of previous posters and doubled the spice, substituting pumpkin pie spice for the cloves & such. With all of my substitutions, it came out really nice. Not too sweet, but sweet enough. It was moist & spicy, and I'll definitely be making this a staple this Fall.

