Rating: 3
Great treat on an October day. The recipe halves nicely (I used two eggs for half the recipe). I also added a cream cheese swirl on top: blend together 1/2 cup cream cheese, 1 egg and 1/4 cup sugar until smooth. Pour 3/4 of pumpkin batter into your loaf pan. Spread cream cheese mix on top evenly. Cover with remaining pumpkin batter. Swirl slightly with knife for marble effect. YUMM.

