Rating: 4
This recipe is (1) incredibly easy to make, and (2) incredibly addictive. Let's not be coy; this is a cake, not a bread. Since I prefer it in more of a snack cake size, I make it in two 8x8 square pans and cut the baking time to about 40 mins. For extra addictive powers, I add a cream cheese frosting or do a cream cheese swirl prior to baking, but it's plenty moist on its own. I always end up taking the second pan to work and it's usually gone by lunch. This is a big payoff for something that requires so little effort (and makes my more elaborate creations feel jealous). Enjoy!

