I've made this bread twice now, the first following the directions exactly and the second with some alterations. It is delicious both ways! I added dried cranberries (as suggested by a previous reviewer) and chopped pecans. I also added more pumpkin, increased the spices x2 and used 1/2 brown sugar and 1/2 granulated. If I had applesauce I'd have used it, however, I did cut back on the oil and still had moist, delicious bread/muffins. My kids (6,4,1) prefer them without nuts/cranberries so I make a batch of each. They are gone in a few days! This will become a regular in our house. As a side note, I personally enjoy reading reviews that contain suggestions or alterations to the original recipe. I find the information very useful, especially when a specific issue (i.e. too sweet, salty, etc.) is mentioned frequently.

