I agree with the below comment, don't change the recipe, try it the way it is first and THEN make changes. I see it all over this site and it drives me NUTS! I made this and followed it exactly as written the first time, which was fantastic. Then I tweeked it, using half brown and half white sugar and leaving out the nuts. Fine crumb, very very moist and flavorful, and I made half of that second batch into mini muffins (it made 24 mini's plus one regular sized loaf) Good for breakfast or snacks, too sweet for dinner.

Rating: 4
I get such a kick out of the people who rate this recipe highly and then go on to tell you how they changed this, that and the other ingredient, so of course it is no longer this recipe at all. Rest assured the recipe is wonderful just as written. It produces a very moist, sweet, richly flavored, cake-like result with a fine crumb. I would find it too sweet to serve with a meal, but great as a dessert or breakfast treat. If you want a "breadier" bread, with less sweetness and a rougher texture, this will disappoint, and you should either seek another version or try some of the variations suggested here.

