This bread is fabulous. I just made it for the second time in as many weeks, and it was a hit both times. I think the oven I used runs hot, but even cutting the temperature and time the second time, it still came out black on the bottom (though not overly dry inside). That is, of course, my fault for not testing it earlier, but I'd recommend checking your bread after perhaps 50 minutes, so that you don't wait until it's cooked too long. I made this with a 15-oz pumpkin jar, simply because that's what they had at the store, but otherwise didn't change anything with the ingredients. I'm sure that you could cut down on the sugar, but I'm perfectly content with this recipe the way it is.

