This recipe is good -- but does not taste enough like pumpkin to give it a 4 forks. In response to those who think only those who made the exact recipe should comment... it would make for a boring read. I often use the suggestions of others to improve the recipe, reading between the lines to try and guess at what it might taste like if the recipe was followed exactly as indicated. Some reader says: "I cut the sugar and it was perfect!" Then I know I'll find the recipe too sweet since I usually cut on sugar too. Some reader says: "I added more spices." Then I'll also add spices, since I love cinnamon and nutmeg too... etc. Imagine everyone commenting on the recipe, as is indicated... it would limit what one had to say. And in this case, I could sum it up as: "too oily, too sweet." Thanks to the experiments and comments of another user who DID NOT follow the recipe as indicated, I partly used buttermilk -- and it saved the recipe.

