Lovely bread - dense, moist and deliciously spicy. No definite pumpkin taste, more like gingerbread. I reduced the sugar to 1 cup white and 1 cup dark demerarra, reduced oil to 1/2 cup and added 1/2 cup sour cream, added 1/4 cup molasses and 1/4 cup dark rum, doubled all the spices and added 1 tsp each allspice, ginger and vanilla. I increased baking powder to 1 tsp, but oops, forgot to add the baking soda, so my loaves didn't rise very well. Nonetheless, a scrumptious bread - excellent with a cup of tea. Also, they were completely done at 50 minutes, so watch your timing - but could have been my oven. Even better the next day - the flavours really mellow and deepen.

