Rating: 3
After making this differently 3x, I recommend a max of 2c sugar (2c is still very sweet). Once I tried 1c brown, 1c white, but the bread came out a little wet. Just FYI, 16 oz canned pumpkin = 1 7/8 c. I also added 1t vanilla to the wet mixture. I increased cinnamon and nutmeg to 2.5t each, added 1/4 t allspice, 1/2 t ground ginger. No need to increase cloves. I recommend increasing the nuts to 1.5 c. Also, decrease baking time! 22 mins for mini-muffins, 40 mins for an 8x4 loaf pan, 45 mins for a 9x5 loaf pan. The bread comes out perfectly soft inside and crunchy on the top.

