I followed the advice of previous reviewers and substituted apple sauce for half the oil, and 1 c. of brown sugar for one of the cups of white sugar. Other changes: I used fresh pumpkin pulp instead of canned, added a cup of cranberries, and made muffins instead of bread. (To make fresh pulp, cut a pumpkin in half, scoop out insides, and roast, open side down, on a greased cookie sheet at 325-350 until soft; 30-60 mins. depending on size; after cool, scoop out pulp and mash with a potato masher or other similar tool; cooked pulp can be frozen.) The results were good. The muffins made a great breakfast, and I gave them to people as treats to take home after Christmas dinner.

