Like many of the other bakers, I reduced the amount of sugar and adjusted the spices to accommodate our household tastes. I also substituted semi-sweet mini-chocolate chips (for maximum chocolate distribution!). Chocolate and pumpkin sounds like a bizarre combo, but I've used them together for years with great success. This is definitely a make-again recipe!

Rating: 4
