I thought this recipe was great. I did substitute unsweetened applesauce for the oil, which worked out very well. And I only used 2 cups of sugar instead of three. I was leery about the applesauce effecting the moistness, but I couldn't believe how moist it was. I would make this again.

Rating: 3
I substituted 1 container of Yoplait (peach flavor, it was all I had in the fridge) and 1/3 C oil for the WHOLE CUP (!) of oil called for, and 1 C of white and 1 C of dark brown sugar for the 3 CUPS (!) of white sugar called for. Oh, yeah--instead of pumpkin I used mashed leftover roasted sweet potato that we had yesterday. The result is yummy.

