Rating: 3
This is a great recipe! I tried it once using the 3 cups of sugar and found it too sweet, so the next time I made it I cut it back to 2 cups and that was just right. I also substituted 1 cup of unsweetened applesauce for the 1 cup of oil to reduce the fat, and it was just as moist as with the oil. Using the applesauce instead of the oil makes this recipe virtually fat free (unless you add the walnuts). I thought the mix of spices was just right, too.

Rating: 3
This recipe helped me get started, but I made a few changes - only 2 cups of sugar and 2 1/2 cups flour. I doubled the spices, and added a 1/2 cup of crystalized ginger. The resulting muffins were fantastic - good flavor and very tender.

