This is my favorite fall recipe. I run a personal chef service and this is what I make for a little something extra for my clients this time of year. They all love it. Beware though: it's so good people will be asking you to sell it to them. I don't change anything, but would like to lighten it up a bit. I do add walnuts to the top only and gently press them in before baking. Today I made 2 double batches of it. My mixer can only handle 2 batches at a time. I had so much batter that I used the extra in muffin tins, which worked out. This stuff is truly addictive. I have also served it as a dessert: warm a piece in microwave, serve with vanilla ice cream with a good apple butter over it. Awesome!!

